=== BUG REPORT: Tokenizer Extension v1 vs v2 ===

PROBLEM (v1):
  Used HuggingFace `tokenizer.add_tokens()` to add 10K new tokens.
  This adds tokens to the vocabulary table but does NOT update BPE merge rules.
  Result: tokenizer never produces new tokens during encoding.
  Fertility stayed at 4.0 tok/word for Kazakh (zero improvement).

ROOT CAUSE:
  add_tokens() is designed for adding special tokens (like <mask>, <sep>)
  that appear literally in text. It's not meant for extending BPE vocabulary.
  BPE tokenizers need merge rules to know HOW to produce a token from characters.

FIX (v2):
  Proper SentencePiece protobuf merge (Chinese-LLaMA method):
  1. Train new SentencePiece BPE on target corpus (learns Kazakh/Russian merge rules)
  2. Parse both .model files as protobuf
  3. Add new pieces (with scores/rules) from new SP into base SP
  4. Save merged protobuf as new tokenizer.model
  This preserves ALL original tokenization while adding new merge rules for target language.

REFERENCE: Chinese-LLaMA-Alpaca-2/scripts/merge_tokenizer/merge_tokenizers.py
